@*
    ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    BnListDemo — Phase 7.2 Task 1.4 (design §"The proof surface"), route
    "/list", mount-registry key "BnListDemo". Authored in .razor (7.1: this
    is how everything new is written).

    A SIXTH page, same rationale as the fourth and fifth: BnScrollDemo's
    frame table IS the 6.2 cross-platform parity contract, and the phase
    that introduces virtualization does not get to rewrite it. This page's
    numbers are ITS OWN contract — asserted by BnListDemoTests (the .NET
    golden) and by Gates 2/3 on the AVD and the iOS simulator, THE SAME
    NUMBERS, because Yoga computes in dp/pt on both.

    ── THE PAGE ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

    500 rows × 64dp in a 300×400 viewport, overscan 4 (the design's
    numbers). Each row: a BnInput whose PLACEHOLDER is "Row i" — the row's
    identity in goldens and screenshots — and which is deliberately UNBOUND:
    text typed into it lives ONLY in the native EditText/UITextField, so a
    recycled (destroyed/recreated) row would visibly LOSE it. That is the
    row-state-travels proof: @key = the item, a surviving row keeps its
    node, its native view, its text and focus, while the window slides
    around it.

    ── THE NUMBERS GATES 2/3 ASSERT (derived, not invented) ─────────────────

      content height   500 × 64 = 32,000 dp   (the synthetic content node's
                                               Yoga-computed height: spacers
                                               + window rows, by construction)
      scroll range     32,000 − 400 = 31,600 dp
      window @ 0       [0, 11)  — ceil(400/64)=7 visible rows + 4 trailing
                                  overscan; leading overscan clamped at 0
      window @ 640     [6, 21)  — 15 live rows: ceil(400/64) + 2×4, the
                                  design's liveness count (640 = 10 rows —
                                  a mid-scroll offset on a row boundary)
      window @ 31,600  [489, 500) — 11 rows; trailing overscan clamped
      spacers @ 0      lead 0,      trail 489 × 64 = 31,296
      spacers @ 640    lead 384,    trail 479 × 64 = 30,656
      spacers @ 31,600 lead 31,296, trail 0

      LIVENESS IS A COUNTED ASSERTION: the scroll node's children (= the
      shells' content-node children) are ALWAYS 2 spacers + the window rows:
        13 at offset 0 · 17 at offset 640 · 13 at offset 31,600.
      Any other child count means virtualization is not virtualizing.

    ── WHAT SLIDING 0 → 640 LOOKS LIKE ON THE WIRE (the .NET golden pins) ───

      rows 0–5 leave   → 12 RemoveNode: the 6 row views + 6 REDUNDANT input
                         removes (each input already left with its row's
                         subtree — the documented EmitDisposedComponentRemoves
                         host contract: a nested child component disposed in
                         the same batch still emits RemoveNode for its root
                         views, and hosts treat unknown ids as a no-op)
      rows 11–20 enter → 20 creates (10 row views + 10 inputs), placeholders
                         "Row 11".."Row 20", inserted BEFORE the trail spacer
      rows 6–10 SURVIVE→ their node ids appear in NO create/remove — and no
                         value/placeholder prop is rewritten on them; their
                         native text/focus is untouched (state travelled)
      spacers resize   → exactly two spacer SetStyles: lead 0→384,
                         trail 31,296→30,656

    The scroll event arrives via the wire contract: name `scroll`, payload
    the offset in dp/pt, conflated by the shell to at most one dispatch per
    committed frame (Gates 2/3 implement the conflation; this page and its
    golden drive the dispatch synthetically through dispatch_event).

    Nav parity with every other page: "← Back" OUTSIDE the viewport →
    INavigationManager → "/". Reachable by mount-name ("BnListDemo") and by
    route ("/list"); no button on BnDemo points here (adding one would churn
    BnDemo's goldens for no engine reason). A fresh ROOT component: no
    cascaded theme crosses a root swap.
    ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*@
<BnColumn>
    @* [0] the virtualized list. TItem=int: the item IS the row index — ints
       are distinct, and @key-by-item boxes them into stable value-equal
       keys. All five numbers come from the internal consts below so the
       golden asserts the PRODUCTS, never a transcription. *@
    <BnList TItem="int"
            Items="@RowItems"
            ItemHeight="@ItemHeightF"
            Height="@ViewportHeightF"
            Width="@ViewportWidth"
            Overscan="@OverscanRows">
        <RowTemplate Context="row">
            @* UNBOUND on purpose — see the header: typed text lives only in
               the native widget, so view identity IS the state proof. The
               placeholder is the row's identity ("Row 17") in goldens,
               device assertions and human screenshots alike. *@
            <BnInput Placeholder="@RowPlaceholder(row)" />
        </RowTemplate>
    </BnList>

    @* [1] nav parity — OUTSIDE the viewport, so no amount of scrolling can
       take the exit off the screen. The page's only measured leaf, LAST. *@
    <BnRow Width="@ViewportWidth">
        <BnButton Label="← Back" OnClick="GoBack" />
    </BnRow>
</BnColumn>

@code {
    // ── THE PAGE'S ARITHMETIC, AS CONSTANTS (the BnScrollDemo discipline) ─────
    //
    // BnListDemoTests asserts the products (RowCount × ItemHeightDp == 32,000;
    // − ViewportHeightDp == 31,600) AND that BnListWindow.Compute reproduces
    // the windows in the header, so a changed number reddens the golden before
    // it desynchronises three file headers. Gates 2/3 read these consts.

    /// <summary>500 rows — big enough that non-virtualized rendering would be
    /// unmissable (500 native EditTexts), small enough to assert exactly.</summary>
    internal const int RowCount = 500;

    /// <summary>Every row is 64dp tall (design decision 3: FIXED — the window
    /// is exact arithmetic). RowCount × this is the content size.</summary>
    internal const int ItemHeightDp = 64;

    /// <summary>The viewport: 300 × 400 (the design's numbers).</summary>
    internal const int ViewportWidthDp = 300;

    /// <inheritdoc cref="ViewportWidthDp"/>
    internal const int ViewportHeightDp = 400;

    /// <summary>Overscan 4: rows rendered beyond the visible span, each side,
    /// clamped at the ends. The liveness count is ceil(400/64) + 2×4 = 15
    /// mid-scroll, 11 at either end.</summary>
    internal const int OverscanRows = 4;

    /// <summary>What the synthetic content node must compute to in Yoga —
    /// 32,000dp. By CONSTRUCTION (spacers + window rows always tile it); the
    /// shells READ it (contentSize), never derive it.</summary>
    internal const int ContentHeightDp = RowCount * ItemHeightDp;

    /// <summary>The scrollable range Gates 2/3 drive: 32,000 − 400 = 31,600.</summary>
    internal const int ScrollRangeDp = ContentHeightDp - ViewportHeightDp;

    /// <summary>The golden's mid-scroll offset: exactly 10 rows down. On a row
    /// boundary on purpose — the window numbers in the header stay clean —
    /// and NOT a multiple of the viewport, so the slide is asymmetric enough
    /// to catch a rows-for-spacers mixup.</summary>
    internal const int MidScrollOffsetDp = 640;

    // Typed mirrors for the markup (razor passes these to BnList's float
    // params; one source of truth, zero transcription).
    private const float ItemHeightF = ItemHeightDp;
    private const float ViewportHeightF = ViewportHeightDp;

    private static readonly string ViewportWidth =
        ViewportWidthDp.ToString(System.Globalization.CultureInfo.InvariantCulture);

    private static readonly int[] RowItems = Enumerable.Range(0, RowCount).ToArray();

    /// <summary>The row's identity string, everywhere: goldens, device
    /// assertions, screenshots. Invariant — "Row 17" on every locale.</summary>
    internal static string RowPlaceholder(int row)
        => string.Create(System.Globalization.CultureInfo.InvariantCulture, $"Row {row}");

    [Inject] public INavigationManager Navigation { get; set; } = default!;

    private Task GoBack() => Navigation.NavigateToAsync("/").AsTask();
}
